BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9OrLOyM_7V17xGSakSXfr
SUMMARY:Seattle DSA Fundraising Drive
DTSTAMP:20260403T051350Z
DTSTART:20260405T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Sunday\\\, April 5th as we make calls to Seattle DSA
	 members and ask them to make monthly contributions to help close our $8\\
	\,500 budget gap this year! \\nSeattle DSA has been working hard this year
	 to protect our neighbors\\\, promote progressive taxes\\\, and fight for 
	a better world. Closing our budget gap will allow us to keep it up\\\, and
	 exceeding our goals would allow us to act even more boldly.  \\nYour frie
	nds and comrades are going to ask members who are currently giving monthly
	 local donations to chip in a bit more each month. We’ll also be calling m
	embers who aren’t yet providing donations to the chapter and asking them t
	o start.  \\nYou’ll be provided a script and a list of people to call. If 
	you’ve ever wondered how you can get people to buy into financially suppor
	ting grassroots projects\\\, this is a great place to start. \\nBeacon Hil
	l library branch\\nLocated right by Beacon Hill Link station\n\nhttps://se
	attledsa.org/event/seattle-dsa-fundraising-drive/\n\nFrom Seattle DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/seattle-dsa-fundraising-drive/
LOCATION:Beacon Hill Branch – Seattle Public Library\\\, 2821 Beacon Ave S\
	\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98144\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-dsa
CATEGORIES:Seattle DSA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:MgSPLtlKiDDb1Ar_GHco8
SUMMARY:Moomins' Sea Adventures & Tove and the Sea
DTSTAMP:20260403T051350Z
DTSTART:20260405T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Dive into the whimsical world of Moominvalley and the life of i
	ts creator\, Tove Jansson\, with *Moomins’ Sea Adventures* and *Tove and t
	he Sea*.\n\n*Moomins’ Sea Adventures* brings Moominvalley to life with ill
	ustrations and life-sized characters from the stories. In the center of th
	e exhibit is an interactive island complete with a lighthouse and rowboats
	 that invites visitors to imagine adventures of their own.\n\n*Tove and th
	e Sea* offers a more intimate counterpoint\, tracing Tove Jansson’s lifelo
	ng relationship with the Finnish archipelago through large-scale photograp
	hs and reflective texts.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/
	moomins-sea-adventures-tove-and-the-sea/18406909/2026-04-05T00\n\nFrom SEA
	today - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/moomins-sea-adventures-to
	ve-and-the-sea/18406909/2026-04-05T00
LOCATION:National Nordic Museum\, 2655 NW Market Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
